WEBVTT

00:41.750 --> 00:43.035
You okay?

00:43.040 --> 00:44.826
Yeah. I just need some fresh air.

00:44.830 --> 00:46.878
I'm going to...
I'm gonna run around a little bit.

00:47.540 --> 00:49.451
I'm gonna be as good as new.

00:51.330 --> 00:54.117
Are we home?

00:54.420 --> 00:56.456
Not yet, buddy. Go back to sleep, okay?

01:12.830 --> 01:14.661
What a goofball.

01:25.880 --> 01:27.029
He fainted.

01:34.790 --> 01:35.996
Matt.

01:36.000 --> 01:37.115
Dad!

01:39.580 --> 01:40.956
Ohh! I got you.

01:40.960 --> 01:42.450
My heart is racing.

01:47.420 --> 01:48.569
What is it?

01:48.580 --> 01:50.070
The car just stopped.

01:52.540 --> 01:53.871
Must be the battery.

01:53.880 --> 01:54.995
Stop fooling around.

01:55.000 --> 01:56.570
No, I'm serious. The car will not start.

01:57.250 --> 01:58.877
At least turn the lights on.

01:58.880 --> 02:00.108
Mom's afraid of the dark.

02:00.120 --> 02:01.200
No, I'm not.

02:10.750 --> 02:11.956
I got you.

02:12.210 --> 02:13.245
I got you.

02:22.210 --> 02:24.917
Hi, hi, hi. Sorry
for the cryptic late-night text,

02:24.920 --> 02:26.956
but I promised I'd fill you in
on the way here,

02:26.960 --> 02:28.916
and I am a girl
who keeps her promises.

02:28.920 --> 02:32.572
So, this boy was found two hours ago
in the middle of nowhere.

02:32.580 --> 02:35.071
Technically, he was found
outside of Crawford, Arizona.

02:35.080 --> 02:37.878
My point is, he has clearly been
to super hell

02:37.880 --> 02:39.609
and escaped some sort of captivity.

02:39.620 --> 02:41.531
How do we know he wasn't
Just dropped off there?

02:41.540 --> 02:44.202
Well, he has fresh cuts
on the bottom of his feet

02:44.210 --> 02:45.450
from the local cactus fields,

02:45.460 --> 02:46.950
and that's away
from any through roads,

02:46.960 --> 02:49.531
and his skin is rubbed raw
around his ankles from chains.

02:49.540 --> 02:51.747
He must've had a chance
to escape and he took it.

02:51.750 --> 02:53.661
Or the UnSub
could have had him in transit.

02:53.670 --> 02:55.615
My God,
you guys, look at his eyes.

02:55.620 --> 02:56.780
Yeah, he's jaundiced.

02:56.790 --> 02:58.451
Probably hasn't seen
daylight in a while.

02:58.460 --> 02:59.916
Yeah, and there's a lot of scars here.

02:59.920 --> 03:01.569
And those are the ones we can see.

03:01.580 --> 03:05.072
It's hard to tell for certain,
but he's maybe 13.

03:05.080 --> 03:07.321
Are there any missing
children in the area, Garcia?

03:07.330 --> 03:08.957
None until now, but, sir,

03:08.960 --> 03:10.325
you may have more information
than I do.

03:10.330 --> 03:13.743
I do. Earlier tonight another boy
was reported missing in Flagstaff.

03:13.750 --> 03:15.991
That's not that far.
It can't be a coincidence.

03:16.000 --> 03:17.160
Technically, it could,

03:17.170 --> 03:19.070
but Arizona has the lowest
abduction rate in the country,

03:19.080 --> 03:22.379
so_the chances of these cases _
not being related are ridiculously slim.

03:22.380 --> 03:23.995
Yeah. That's why
Child Abduction Rapid Deployment

03:24.000 --> 03:25.115
will meet you on the ground.

03:25.120 --> 03:27.827
The Flagstaff abduction
is Billy Henderson, 13.

03:27.830 --> 03:30.321
His parents say he was coming back
from a friend's house after dinner.

03:30.330 --> 03:31.456
He never made it.

03:31.460 --> 03:32.575
Okay, they set up roadblocks,

03:32.580 --> 03:33.786
but the UnSub has a head start.

03:33.790 --> 03:35.997
Right now our best chance
of finding Billy Henderson

03:36.000 --> 03:37.877
is to figure out
what the first victim knows.

03:37.880 --> 03:40.166
Exactly. 50, Morgan,
you and JJ go to the hospital,

03:40.170 --> 03:41.614
see if you can get through to him.

03:41.620 --> 03:43.167
The rest of us will set up
at the police station.

03:43.710 --> 03:45.826
Losing his victim has likely
enraged the UnSub.

03:46.620 --> 03:48.497
No telling what he'll do to Billy.

03:54.920 --> 03:55.955
No!

03:57.250 --> 03:58.410
Please!

03:58.830 --> 04:00.206
Please...

04:00.540 --> 04:02.076
Please, no!

04:35.330 --> 04:37.912
"Memory is
a complicated thing,

04:37.920 --> 04:40.662
"a relative to truth, but not its twin."

04:40.960 --> 04:42.530
Barbara Kingsolver.

04:42.540 --> 04:44.952
Apparently,
Billy was riding his bike home

04:44.960 --> 04:46.200
from his friend's house last night.

04:46.460 --> 04:47.666
They find the bike?

04:47.670 --> 04:49.956
No, the UnSub was smart enough
to cover his tracks.

04:49.960 --> 04:51.996
And he has the guts to take a good kid

04:52.000 --> 04:53.661
from a decent neighborhood.

04:53.670 --> 04:55.991
20 pm.

04:56.000 --> 04:57.991
The ride home
was less than a half a mile.

04:59.210 --> 05:00.825
You're on speaker, Garcia.

05:00.830 --> 05:02.377
Okay,
I got the whole gang on.

05:02.380 --> 05:03.995
It looks like the first victim

05:04.000 --> 05:05.911
was definitely held in captivity

05:05.920 --> 05:07.706
-in Crawford, Arizona.-Why is that?

05:07.710 --> 05:10.281
Because a woman walked
into Crawford P.D. this morning

05:10.290 --> 05:13.248
says she remembers a boy
in chains, in Crawford,

05:13.250 --> 05:14.569
30 years ago.

05:14.580 --> 05:16.377
Just like the boy found last night.

05:16.380 --> 05:17.699
Is she still at the station?

05:17.710 --> 05:19.496
No. She dropped
that bomb of information

05:19.500 --> 05:20.660
and then she took off.

05:20.670 --> 05:22.991
Her name's Samantha Allen.

05:23.000 --> 05:25.207
Most documents have her
listed as Sam Allen.

05:25.210 --> 05:27.747
36, never married, born and raised

05:27.750 --> 05:29.377
and lived her whole life in Crawford,

05:29.380 --> 05:31.109
owns and operates a nursery,

05:31.120 --> 05:32.576
the plant kind, not the baby kind.

05:32.580 --> 05:34.992
Mother died when she was 5,
dad's a real estate developer.

05:35.000 --> 05:36.490
Is there security footage?

05:36.500 --> 05:37.740
Yes. I'm sending that to you.

05:37.750 --> 05:39.240
It's on your tablets right now.

05:40.750 --> 05:43.412
What's she looking at?
ROSSI: I can't tell.

05:48.000 --> 05:50.241
What happened?-It looks like she was spooked.

05:50.250 --> 05:51.376
Dave, you and Prentiss

05:51.380 --> 05:52.665
see if you can find Samantha Allen.

05:52.670 --> 05:54.570
Reid and I will get set up at the station.

05:54.580 --> 05:57.538
All we can hope is that Morgan
and JJ get through to the survivor.

05:59.420 --> 06:00.956
You can't examine the scars?

06:00.960 --> 06:02.075
I can't get close enough.

06:02.080 --> 06:04.617
He has the most severe case
of CER I've ever seen.

06:04.620 --> 06:06.201
Conditioned emotional response.

06:06.210 --> 06:07.700
I've only seen it in vets.

06:07.710 --> 06:09.246
That's worse than PTSD.

06:09.250 --> 06:10.877
He had an adrenaline rush
when he escaped,

06:10.880 --> 06:13.075
but coming down from that
will be just as extreme.

06:13.080 --> 06:15.036
And I'm sure he's
sensitive to light and sound.

06:15.040 --> 06:17.417
Incredibly. We're keeping it
as quiet and dark as possible.

06:17.420 --> 06:18.614
It's probably what he's used to.

06:18.620 --> 06:20.110
He's also been somewhere cramped.

06:20.120 --> 06:22.418
His legs show signs
of advanced arthritis.

06:22.420 --> 06:23.876
Any idea how old he is?

06:23.880 --> 06:25.825
It's hard to tell.
His growth has been stunted.

06:25.830 --> 06:27.707
He's got major tooth and skin decay,

06:27.710 --> 06:29.871
clearly from a massive
vitamin D deficiency.

06:29.880 --> 06:31.074
Best guess?

06:32.540 --> 06:33.575
Maybe 16.

07:05.750 --> 07:06.876
Hey.

07:08.380 --> 07:10.029
My name's Derek.

07:10.040 --> 07:11.416
I'm one of the good guys.

07:12.250 --> 07:13.660
And this is my friend.

07:13.670 --> 07:14.910
I'm Jennifer.

07:15.330 --> 07:17.070
You're safe now.

07:17.330 --> 07:19.207
Doctor says
you haven't been eating much.

07:20.420 --> 07:21.910
Food looks pretty good.

07:23.250 --> 07:24.990
You must be thirsty.

07:25.750 --> 07:26.876
Here you go.

07:28.290 --> 07:29.917
Okay. It's okay.

07:30.250 --> 07:31.456
It's okay.

07:32.120 --> 07:34.031
JJ, this is years of conditioning.

07:35.290 --> 07:37.747
Have Garcia go back
to 2000 for missing kids.

07:37.750 --> 07:38.785
Yeah.

07:50.750 --> 07:52.069
Detective, I'm Agent Hotchner.

07:52.080 --> 07:54.287
-Detective Perez.
-This is Dr. Reid.

07:54.290 --> 07:55.575
I thought your team was bigger.

07:55.580 --> 07:57.070
The rest are following other leads.

07:57.080 --> 07:58.616
Is CARD retracing the escape route

07:58.620 --> 07:59.826
that the boy in chains took?

07:59.830 --> 08:01.206
They have been canvassing all night.

08:01.500 --> 08:02.910
There's another team in Flagstaff

08:02.920 --> 08:04.706
retracing Billy Henderson's bike ride.

08:04.710 --> 08:05.950
Where are Billy's parents?

08:05.960 --> 08:07.700
Chief's office.
-Thank you.

08:08.040 --> 08:09.951
Detective, you talked
to Sam Allen over here

08:09.960 --> 08:11.700
and it looked like one of
these photos upset her.

08:11.710 --> 08:13.325
Do you have any idea why?

08:13.670 --> 08:15.706
-Yeah, well it's weird.
-Why's that?

08:15.710 --> 08:17.826
Because most of these people
have passed away.

08:18.120 --> 08:20.111
That's our old chief.

08:20.120 --> 08:22.327
That one there, he built the station

08:22.330 --> 08:23.820
and some of the houses around here.

08:24.170 --> 08:25.535
It's J.B. Allen,

08:25.540 --> 08:26.780
Sam's father.

08:39.790 --> 08:41.496
Hi, there. Can I help you?

08:41.500 --> 08:43.206
We're with the FBI.

08:43.710 --> 08:46.326
We heard you were at
the police station earlier.

08:46.330 --> 08:49.879
I told the other detective,
that was a mistake.

08:50.250 --> 08:53.242
Why did you leave the station
when you saw you father's photo?

08:53.250 --> 08:54.376
I didn't.

08:54.380 --> 08:55.995
We saw the security footage.

08:56.380 --> 08:59.281
You told them you saw a boy in chains
when you were a kid.

09:00.210 --> 09:02.826
Why do you think your father
had something to do with this?

09:02.830 --> 09:04.661
He doesn't. I never said that.

09:04.670 --> 09:06.456
My father is a good man.

09:07.250 --> 09:09.491
This isn't about him, okay?

09:09.500 --> 09:12.287
I told the other detective,
I made a mistake.

09:13.250 --> 09:14.911
You know what I think?

09:15.540 --> 09:17.701
I think you saw the news
coverage of that little boy

09:17.710 --> 09:20.452
they found last night,
and it triggered something.

09:20.710 --> 09:23.281
If you know anything that can help us

09:23.290 --> 09:25.076
and you're keeping it to yourself,

09:25.080 --> 09:27.708
that's as_horrendous _
as what's happening to those children.

09:27.710 --> 09:29.416
Look, I'm sorry.

09:29.790 --> 09:31.576
I really, really am.

09:31.960 --> 09:34.451
But I... I can't help you.

09:39.290 --> 09:40.416
Come on, Randy.

10:04.250 --> 10:06.411
Listen, I know how scared you are.

10:06.880 --> 10:08.666
I know you think he can still hurt you,

10:08.670 --> 10:10.319
that he's just outside that door.

10:10.330 --> 10:11.957
But I promise you he's not.

10:13.500 --> 10:14.615
Even if he was,

10:14.620 --> 10:16.497
he'd have to get through me
to get to you,

10:17.250 --> 10:19.571
and I'm not about to let that happen.

10:42.040 --> 10:43.871
_ So it sounds like _
Billy's always been cautious.

10:43.880 --> 10:46.701
He's our oldest.
And he follows the rules.

10:47.000 --> 10:48.786
It drives his little sister crazy

10:48.790 --> 10:50.417
'cause she's the opposite.

10:51.210 --> 10:52.416
And he rides his bike a lot?

10:52.420 --> 10:54.115
All the time.

10:54.120 --> 10:55.280
Even at night?

10:55.290 --> 10:56.996
He's got lights and reflectors.

10:57.000 --> 11:00.072
He even has a headlamp on his helmet.

11:00.420 --> 11:02.376
We used to ride with him, but he's 13.

11:04.080 --> 11:06.878
He was only two streets over.

11:07.620 --> 11:09.611
And you feel pretty certain
that he wouldn't go anywhere

11:09.620 --> 11:10.780
with a stranger?

11:10.790 --> 11:12.667
No. No way. Never.

11:13.500 --> 11:15.491
If someone asked for help,
would he stop?

11:15.500 --> 11:16.615
Hold on.

11:16.620 --> 11:18.497
Are you saying that Billy
was taken because he's polite?

11:18.500 --> 11:21.822
I'm not saying
that it's his fault or yours.

11:22.790 --> 11:24.166
Billy is a cautious child,

11:24.170 --> 11:25.876
and that will be his strength right now.

11:54.830 --> 11:56.411
She left after seeing
a photo of her father?

11:56.420 --> 11:57.535
Did she accuse him?

11:57.540 --> 11:59.110
No, the opposite. She protected him.

11:59.120 --> 12:00.701
Garcia ran her mental health history.

12:00.960 --> 12:02.746
She had some grief counseling
after her mother died,

12:02.750 --> 12:04.286
but other than that, no therapy.

12:04.880 --> 12:06.950
We can talk to her but
we can't force her to help.

12:06.960 --> 12:09.326
No, but something in her gut
brought her in here.

12:09.330 --> 12:10.877
If there's any truth to her instincts,

12:10.880 --> 12:12.609
there's gonna be some kind
of a record of a missing boy

12:12.620 --> 12:13.780
from 30 years ago.

12:13.790 --> 12:15.496
Well, have Garcia
check unsolved cases

12:15.500 --> 12:17.286
and also check into J.B. Allen's history.

12:17.290 --> 12:19.417
-We can't rule anybody out.
-Okay.

12:19.420 --> 12:21.160
How are Morgan and JJ
doing with the boy?

12:21.420 --> 12:23.456
He's so traumatized,
he can't even speak.

12:25.540 --> 12:27.201
Give me everything
you have on J.B. Allen

12:27.210 --> 12:29.326
and also all of the unsolved missings.

12:29.330 --> 12:32.117
You know what,
go back to 1980 just to cover bases.

12:32.620 --> 12:33.780
Thanks, Garcia.

12:52.960 --> 12:55.326
It's okay. It's okay.

13:02.710 --> 13:04.325
What did Garcia find out?

13:05.000 --> 13:06.536
She broadened her search,

13:06.540 --> 13:08.781
but nothing
that matches his description.

13:10.580 --> 13:12.491
Somebody's gotta be missing this kid.

13:14.120 --> 13:15.826
No, hey, hey, no. No, no.

13:15.830 --> 13:17.240
That's not for us. That's not for us.

13:17.250 --> 13:18.740
It's for the doctors outside.

13:18.750 --> 13:20.615
It's for the doctors, not for us.

13:21.040 --> 13:22.325
It's all right.

13:22.750 --> 13:24.706
It's okay. It's not for us.

13:26.040 --> 13:27.746
There you go. Come on back.

13:27.750 --> 13:29.820
Here. Just take it.

13:32.540 --> 13:33.780
There you go.

13:35.460 --> 13:38.952
I got him to nod,

13:38.960 --> 13:41.417
but not much more than that.

13:42.000 --> 13:43.536
And you asked him his name?

13:44.040 --> 13:45.075
Yeah.

13:45.620 --> 13:47.497
What about in Spanish?

13:47.500 --> 13:49.456
It doesn't matter the language
if he won't talk.

14:05.620 --> 14:06.951
What's your name, sweetheart?

14:10.380 --> 14:12.109
Can I see what you have there?

14:13.540 --> 14:14.575
Ah.

14:14.880 --> 14:16.529
Do you like eagles?

14:20.880 --> 14:24.077
Yeah, the wings are beautiful,
aren't they?

14:28.080 --> 14:30.492
Your back

14:30.960 --> 14:33.076
Wings on your back...

14:35.500 --> 14:36.535
Angel?

14:38.040 --> 14:39.416
Is your name Angel?

14:49.880 --> 14:51.916
So, softball,
basketball, and soccer.

14:52.210 --> 14:53.871
You played a lot of team sports.

14:53.880 --> 14:54.995
Was your dad a coach?

14:55.000 --> 14:57.992
No. He was always too busy with work.

14:58.000 --> 14:59.911
I guess that's why he kept me busy.

15:00.250 --> 15:01.569
It was okay, though.

15:01.960 --> 15:03.780
The house was too quiet
after Mom died.

15:04.210 --> 15:05.529
She had cancer.

15:06.120 --> 15:08.168
I didn't really know
what that meant growing up,

15:08.170 --> 15:12.288
just that she wasn't gonna get
any better.

15:13.250 --> 15:14.456
Okay.

15:14.960 --> 15:16.279
Let's start with today.

15:17.000 --> 15:18.410
What brought you in here?

15:18.420 --> 15:21.617
I saw that... That boy on the news.

15:23.380 --> 15:25.245
And I saw...

15:25.620 --> 15:27.030
I can't really explain it.

15:27.040 --> 15:31.079
It was like a movie in fast-forward.

15:32.880 --> 15:34.529
It was dark.

15:35.460 --> 15:36.950
So dark.

15:38.290 --> 15:40.326
And that... That little boy,

15:40.330 --> 15:44.118
he had the same chains on his ankles.

15:46.670 --> 15:48.991
And then it was over.

15:49.750 --> 15:52.162
Those flashes that I saw.

15:52.500 --> 15:53.706
That boy...

15:56.380 --> 15:57.608
Was he real?

15:57.620 --> 15:59.247
That's what we need to find out.

16:07.620 --> 16:08.746
Thanks, JJ.

16:08.750 --> 16:09.876
Is the boy talking?

16:09.880 --> 16:11.825
No, but they figured out
that his name is Angel.

16:11.830 --> 16:14.037
Garcia sent a list
of all missing kids since 1980

16:14.040 --> 16:15.610
with a concentration
in the southwest US.

16:15.620 --> 16:17.030
Most are runaways.

16:17.040 --> 16:18.325
All right, let's eliminate the runaways

16:18.330 --> 16:19.991
and focus on lower-risk victims.

16:20.000 --> 16:21.536
Whoever's doing this
likes the challenge.

16:21.540 --> 16:23.531
Here's the thing.
This UnSub is too controlled

16:23.540 --> 16:24.871
to let his victims escape.

16:24.880 --> 16:26.074
I think Angel must have found a way

16:26.080 --> 16:27.877
_ because he was
beIng transferred somewhere.

16:27.880 --> 16:29.416
I'm running out of options here.

16:29.420 --> 16:31.661
The state troopers
are eliminating roadblocks,

16:31.670 --> 16:33.206
and CARD is coming up empty.

16:33.210 --> 16:34.666
If J.B. Allen is a suspect,

16:34.670 --> 16:36.661
why aren't we just kicking down
his door?

16:36.670 --> 16:37.876
Because it's too rislq.

16:37.880 --> 16:39.279
If Allen is who we're looking for,

16:39.290 --> 16:41.702
he has a psychiatric disorder
that drives everything he does.

16:41.710 --> 16:43.450
He'll do whatever it takes to hide Billy,

16:43.460 --> 16:44.609
but he'll sacrifice him

16:44.620 --> 16:46.281
if it means protecting his own freedom.

16:46.290 --> 16:48.952
Everything that this
UnSub does is methodical.

16:48.960 --> 16:50.916
He had a secure place
to keep Angel for years,

16:50.920 --> 16:53.115
but when Angel escaped,
he didn't mourn his loss.

16:53.120 --> 16:54.451
He drove straight to Flagstaff.

16:54.750 --> 16:56.820
The questions is,
why did he choose Flagstaff?

16:56.830 --> 16:58.411
He'd only drive 60 miles out of his way

16:58.420 --> 16:59.956
if he knew someone was there
to make him feel better.

16:59.960 --> 17:01.780
We don't think that Billy
was a victim of opportunity.

17:01.790 --> 17:02.996
We think he was the target.

17:03.000 --> 17:04.615
So this isn't a stranger abduction.

17:04.620 --> 17:06.417
Chances are
he'd seen Angel before, too.

17:06.420 --> 17:07.569
The question is,

17:07.580 --> 17:09.662
where would he have access
to both of these children?

17:12.580 --> 17:14.241
Who should we be looking at?

17:14.710 --> 17:17.326
Friends, neighbors,
coaches, other parents.

17:17.710 --> 17:20.167
We believe that this man
has met Billy before.

17:20.170 --> 17:25.073
VVhat

17:25.080 --> 17:27.571
I'm saying he talked to him
long enough to earn his trust.

17:28.540 --> 17:31.418
But the other little boy,
the one that you just found,

17:31.420 --> 17:33.285
I mean, why don't you ask him
who's doing this?

17:33.830 --> 17:35.912
He's not talking to us yet.

17:36.540 --> 17:38.326
Oh, my God.

17:38.330 --> 17:40.036
Well, what happened to him?

17:43.330 --> 17:44.820
Oh, my God!

17:47.080 --> 17:48.911
That's right. That's right. Bring it over.

17:50.290 --> 17:52.201
Angel, that's pretty good, my man.
You got it.

17:52.500 --> 17:53.785
Keep going.

17:54.170 --> 17:56.115
Okay, please tell me
you found something.

17:56.120 --> 17:57.496
