19:27.120 --> 19:29.031
I'd like you to close your eyes.

19:29.830 --> 19:31.070
Please.

19:32.210 --> 19:33.950
Close your eyes.

19:34.210 --> 19:36.326
Concentrate on your breathing.

19:38.290 --> 19:39.780
-Okay.

19:39.790 --> 19:41.610
You said it was dark.

19:42.330 --> 19:44.571
You were in your pajamas.

19:44.580 --> 19:46.957
Yes. I was burning up.

19:47.880 --> 19:49.529
You probably had a fever.

19:49.540 --> 19:51.076
What did you do?

19:51.080 --> 19:52.820
I called out for my mom,

19:53.290 --> 19:55.451
but she wasn't strong enough,

19:55.880 --> 19:58.110
so I got into bed with her.

19:58.120 --> 19:59.951
Was your dad there?
-No.

20:01.080 --> 20:03.241
Did you hear anything?

20:03.250 --> 20:04.786
My mom's breathing.

20:05.750 --> 20:07.240
Was she having trouble?

20:07.580 --> 20:08.990
Yes.

20:09.000 --> 20:10.991
It's a strange sound.

20:11.460 --> 20:13.951
Was there
another noise in the house?

20:15.080 --> 20:18.868
There's something else,
but I can't see anything.

20:18.880 --> 20:20.108
I followed it.

20:20.120 --> 20:22.281
My feet are so cold.

20:22.290 --> 20:23.826
Because you were outside?

20:23.830 --> 20:25.912
No. The basement.

20:28.380 --> 20:29.916
I see him.

20:29.920 --> 20:31.785
No, I was too scared.

20:31.790 --> 20:34.532
No, no.
I go back up to my parents' bedroom.

20:34.790 --> 20:36.872
Mommy. Mommy.

20:36.880 --> 20:39.075
But I peeked out the window.

20:42.120 --> 20:44.281
And there's the boy.

20:44.290 --> 20:45.746
What is he doing?

20:50.540 --> 20:52.952
He's trying
to get out of that truck.

20:52.960 --> 20:54.370
He's trying to get out of...

20:55.580 --> 20:57.491
Is your dad driving the truck?

20:57.500 --> 20:59.741
-No, no. He couldn't have done this.
-Okay.

20:59.750 --> 21:01.911
You don't understand.
He raised me in that house.

21:01.920 --> 21:04.821
He couldn't have been
doing that all these years.

21:04.830 --> 21:06.616
_ -No!
Okay. Okay.

21:06.620 --> 21:08.611
J.B.'s friends with the whole town.

21:08.960 --> 21:10.416
Never remarried.

21:10.420 --> 21:11.785
Raised Sam by himself.

21:12.670 --> 21:14.570
That's why this is so painful for her.

21:15.000 --> 21:16.740
She doesn't want to believe
that he's capable of it,

21:16.750 --> 21:18.490
but her memory's telling her differently.

21:18.500 --> 21:19.569
So you believe her?

21:20.620 --> 21:23.748
It's very hard to fake
visceral reactions like that.

21:24.460 --> 21:26.109
Yeah, but she's talking about a time

21:26.120 --> 21:27.496
of serious trauma,

21:27.960 --> 21:30.497
on a night she climbed into
bed with her dying mother.

21:30.500 --> 21:32.536
That plus her age,

21:32.540 --> 21:35.077
it's the perfect storm
for a recovered memory.

21:35.330 --> 21:37.457
Wasn't that a huge therapy trend
in the '805?

21:38.750 --> 21:42.868
A lot of women manufactured memories
of their fathers doing horrific things.

21:42.880 --> 21:44.416
And a lot of misguided therapists

21:44.420 --> 21:46.206
_con_vinced them
that their nightmares were real.

21:46.500 --> 21:48.821
It was a huge waste of our resources.

21:49.290 --> 21:51.918
I'm just not sure about this.

21:52.580 --> 21:54.571
I think she's credible enough to warrant

21:54.580 --> 21:56.491
discreet rolling surveillance.

21:57.210 --> 21:59.246
You'll have to use your own team,

21:59.250 --> 22:01.206
'cause he'd recognize
members of this force.

22:01.210 --> 22:03.997
If he has Billy, he won't
hesitate to get rid of him.

22:04.000 --> 22:06.116
I'll get a CARD team member
to join Reid.

22:06.120 --> 22:08.111
Allen can't know we suspect him.

22:16.000 --> 22:17.376
You know, if J.B. Allen is our UnSub,

22:17.380 --> 22:19.109
he certainly doesn't seem unhinged.

22:19.120 --> 22:20.326
He went to the market today,

22:20.330 --> 22:21.820
and he stopped by
his daughter's nursery,

22:21.830 --> 22:23.957
and right now
I'm watching him landscaping.

22:23.960 --> 22:25.746
-At his house?-Yeah.

22:25.750 --> 22:27.035
Is it isolated?

22:27.040 --> 22:28.701
Incredibly isolated.
There's a lot of land.

22:28.710 --> 22:30.871
You remember
what Garcia sent us on J.B. Allen?

22:30.880 --> 22:34.202
He started his contracting business
in 1975,

22:34.210 --> 22:36.030
married Sam's mom that same year.

22:36.040 --> 22:37.576
She died when Sam was 5, as we know.

22:37.580 --> 22:38.911
He never remarried,

22:38.920 --> 22:40.285
and despite
the newer subdivisions he built,

22:40.290 --> 22:42.326
he stayed in the house
he shared with his wife.

22:42.330 --> 22:44.070
So he's either sentimental,

22:44.080 --> 22:45.911
or he didn't sell because
he's customized the house

22:45.920 --> 22:47.205
to hide his victims.

22:47.210 --> 22:48.700
Do you think Angel blames himself?

22:50.580 --> 22:51.911
I know I did.

22:53.420 --> 22:55.115
You know, seeing his mom
for the first time

22:55.120 --> 22:56.610
may not go well.

22:57.460 --> 22:59.496
Well, right now it's just
about the shame he's feeling.

22:59.500 --> 23:02.242
She's gonna have to realize that
he may not want to see her for a while.

23:04.830 --> 23:06.457
Angel. Angel?

23:06.460 --> 23:07.575
Angel, no, no! Angel, no, no!

23:07.920 --> 23:10.787
-Angel, stop! Stop! Stop! Stop!

23:10.790 --> 23:12.166
It's okay.

23:12.170 --> 23:13.910
JJ, get a towel. It's okay.

23:13.920 --> 23:15.456
Angel, listen to me. You're safe.

23:15.460 --> 23:17.109
You're safe. It's okay.

23:17.120 --> 23:18.997
Angel, you're safe.

23:19.000 --> 23:20.877
It's all right.

23:28.710 --> 23:31.782
Please. He's right there.
I have to. I have to see him.

23:32.120 --> 23:34.327
I thought he was gone all these years.

23:34.330 --> 23:35.570
My sweet boy.

23:35.580 --> 23:37.616
Don't you understand?
I need to hold him.

23:37.880 --> 23:39.416
Okay. Listen.

23:40.380 --> 23:43.452
Angel hasn't been held
in a very long time.

23:43.460 --> 23:45.951
Things happened to him.

23:46.460 --> 23:48.200
He's going to have a hard time at first.

23:48.750 --> 23:50.115
Come on.

24:00.620 --> 24:02.281
I know this isn't easy for you.

24:03.500 --> 24:06.071
IfI accuse him and he's done nothing...

24:06.960 --> 24:08.370
Then I've betrayed him.

24:08.380 --> 24:12.248
But if he has, you'll save a young boy.

24:12.500 --> 24:15.412
The best way for you to recover
more of your memory

24:15.420 --> 24:18.662
is to return to the source
of the InItIal sensory trigger.

24:18.670 --> 24:19.989
That was the basement.

24:20.000 --> 24:21.661
How do I explain going down there?

24:21.670 --> 24:23.490
Did he have anything of yours
down there?

24:24.580 --> 24:25.706
Yeah.

24:25.710 --> 24:27.166
See if you can get it back.

24:36.120 --> 24:37.530
Help!

24:37.540 --> 24:39.280
Help!

24:39.290 --> 24:41.030
Help!

24:41.960 --> 24:44.201
Please help me!

24:44.210 --> 24:46.952
-I have to help my boy.
-And you will.

24:47.290 --> 24:48.700
But first, we need your help.

24:49.000 --> 24:50.956
Someone else's little boy is missing.

24:50.960 --> 24:52.666
We're trying to find out
how this man knew

24:52.670 --> 24:54.877
both your son and Billy, and to do that,

24:55.670 --> 24:59.242
I need to know everything that
happened the day Angel disappeared.

24:59.250 --> 25:01.377
It was a Tuesday,

25:01.380 --> 25:02.745
after school.

25:03.420 --> 25:06.287
The children were in the front yard.

25:06.880 --> 25:08.916
It started raining,

25:09.710 --> 25:12.702
but Angel never came back in.

25:13.460 --> 25:15.371
Did you see anyone talking to them?

25:15.380 --> 25:18.497
No. No cars. Nothing.

25:22.580 --> 25:26.209
The neighbors,
the neighbors helped me look.

25:26.210 --> 25:28.417
I wanted to tell the authorities.

25:28.420 --> 25:29.785
I really did.

25:32.580 --> 25:34.457
But we'd have to leave the country

25:34.460 --> 25:36.951
and I had to think of my entire family.

25:44.000 --> 25:45.536
You just have to talk to him, Sam.

25:46.290 --> 25:47.917
You can do this.

25:47.920 --> 25:49.035
Right.

26:06.580 --> 26:08.116
Dad?

26:08.960 --> 26:10.279
You home?

26:10.290 --> 26:12.030
Back here!

26:15.580 --> 26:17.161
-Hey.
-Hey.

26:17.170 --> 26:19.536
-The yard looks good.
-Oh, thanks.

26:19.920 --> 26:22.320
The kids at _the store said
you were gomg to Phoenix,

26:22.330 --> 26:24.821
but I saw your truck
down at the police station.

26:25.540 --> 26:28.668
Oh, yeah.
Their order for potted palms came in,

26:28.670 --> 26:31.878
so I just...
I dropped it off at the station.

26:32.500 --> 26:34.491
Chili. You want a bowl?

26:34.500 --> 26:36.991
It smells great, Dad, but I can't stay.

26:37.460 --> 26:39.872
Since when? It's my chili.

26:40.250 --> 26:42.241
He's not trying to get her out of there.

26:42.250 --> 26:43.410
Not yet.

26:43.420 --> 26:45.991
Hey, is my old catcher's mitt
still down in the basement?

26:46.290 --> 26:47.700
Yeah. Why?

26:47.960 --> 26:50.326
I was thinking about coaching
softball down at the rec.

26:50.790 --> 26:52.667
Yeah? That's great.

26:52.670 --> 26:54.877
You still got the home run record,
you know.

26:54.880 --> 26:56.324
Yeah, I know.

26:56.330 --> 26:58.161
That practice paid off, huh?

26:58.960 --> 27:00.996
Is it... It's still in the bin?

27:01.000 --> 27:02.956
Yeah. Let me get it.
-No, that's okay. I got it.

27:03.960 --> 27:05.666
Uh...I don't think so.

27:05.670 --> 27:07.285
I got boxes everywhere.

27:07.580 --> 27:10.322
I've been trying to
sort through some things.

27:10.330 --> 27:12.457
I'm thinking of having
a yard sale next week.

27:12.460 --> 27:13.779
You want in?

27:13.790 --> 27:15.997
Sounds good, but come on. I can get it.

27:17.040 --> 27:18.996
Suit yourself.

27:43.500 --> 27:45.115
He let her go down there.

27:45.120 --> 27:47.168
Yeah, but he hesitated.

27:47.170 --> 27:49.957
He's not acting like he's got
something to hide, Emily.

27:49.960 --> 27:51.996
That's how he's gotten away with it.

27:52.000 --> 27:53.115
We don't know that.

28:03.330 --> 28:05.491
You find it?

28:06.580 --> 28:08.957
'Cause it's right over here.

28:09.380 --> 28:11.280
Thanks.

28:11.880 --> 28:13.700
Told you it was a mess down here.

28:13.710 --> 28:15.200
Yeah. Yeah.

28:17.210 --> 28:18.450
You sure you can't stay?

28:18.460 --> 28:20.109
Yeah. I'm not feeling great

28:20.120 --> 28:21.667
and I gotta get up early tomorrow.

28:23.000 --> 28:24.240
You going to Phoenix?

28:24.250 --> 28:26.957
Uh, pickups, deliveries.
It'll be a long one.

28:26.960 --> 28:27.995
Uh-huh.

28:30.880 --> 28:33.030
Okay, then. See you later, peanut.

28:33.040 --> 28:34.667
Later, Dad.

29:03.710 --> 29:04.870
I'm so sorry.

29:05.170 --> 29:07.206
It's okay. You did everything we asked.

29:08.040 --> 29:09.325
There was nothing
in the basement.

29:09.330 --> 29:10.536
I'm sorry.

29:14.540 --> 29:15.871
Now all we've got is the kid.

29:31.000 --> 29:33.412
It's called a challenge coin, Angel.

29:33.420 --> 29:36.412
Legend says an American pilot
in World War I

29:36.420 --> 29:38.069
