30:32.290 --> 30:35.168
Angel,
the man who took you took another boy,

30:35.170 --> 30:37.206
and we have to find him.

30:37.210 --> 30:38.450
Can you help us do that?

31:02.710 --> 31:03.995
Angel,

31:04.710 --> 31:06.371
I want you to have this.

31:06.960 --> 31:08.666
It's kept me safe.

31:12.580 --> 31:14.161
Listen to me.

31:17.500 --> 31:19.377
Carl Buford.

31:20.460 --> 31:22.576
That's the name of the man
who hurt me.

31:23.420 --> 31:25.820
I was just a young boy like you, Angel.

31:25.830 --> 31:28.572
And I thought about doing that
very same thing to myself.

31:28.580 --> 31:29.706
I did.

31:30.750 --> 31:33.071
Because the shame was too much.

31:34.670 --> 31:37.070
But instead,

31:37.080 --> 31:39.708
I kept the pain buried inside of me.

31:40.830 --> 31:42.878
And it tore me apart.

31:43.460 --> 31:46.873
But, Angel, I never let
that son of a bitch beat me.

31:48.380 --> 31:50.109
I never gave him that.

31:50.790 --> 31:53.953
I want to make this man pay
for what he's done to you.

31:54.290 --> 31:56.030
But I need your help.

31:57.830 --> 31:59.661
I promise you

31:59.670 --> 32:02.207
that whoever hurt you will not win.

32:02.670 --> 32:04.911
You and me together

32:05.330 --> 32:07.707
can take away what he kept from you

32:07.710 --> 32:10.372
and what he values the most,
and that's freedom.

32:12.120 --> 32:14.202
Angel, please.

32:15.710 --> 32:17.746
Will you help me do that?

32:19.210 --> 32:20.450
Yes.

32:24.290 --> 32:25.826
Can you tell us

32:26.460 --> 32:28.997
if any of these men look familiar?

32:34.080 --> 32:35.570
No.

32:35.920 --> 32:38.070
It was always too dark.

32:42.960 --> 32:45.246
-How do you feel?
-Like I failed.

32:45.830 --> 32:47.240
You didn't.

32:48.170 --> 32:50.115
I failed him.

32:50.960 --> 32:53.246
I actually thought he
could have done all of this.

32:54.540 --> 32:56.201
I think it took more

32:56.210 --> 32:58.576
than a buried memory to come in here.

32:58.880 --> 33:01.747
There is something
about your father's behavior,

33:02.830 --> 33:04.957
things he has said and done

33:05.460 --> 33:07.280
that have bothered you for a long time.

33:07.670 --> 33:09.319
You buried those.

33:10.040 --> 33:11.576
Just like the memory.

33:13.380 --> 33:14.824
Look”.

33:15.880 --> 33:19.873
You lost your mother
when you were very young.

33:20.790 --> 33:22.371
It would have been too devastating

33:22.380 --> 33:24.450
to lose your father as well.

33:25.500 --> 33:28.742
Repressing those memories
is a defense mechanism.

33:28.750 --> 33:30.160
So, um...

33:32.380 --> 33:34.245
What else did I bury?

33:34.920 --> 33:36.820
His mood swings, probably.

33:37.330 --> 33:41.778
Do you remember when
he was happy one day, angry the next?

33:44.000 --> 33:45.376
Yeah.

33:46.830 --> 33:48.912
And when his moods were extreme,

33:49.330 --> 33:51.070
did he give you gifts?

33:55.460 --> 33:56.870
How do you know that?

33:57.500 --> 33:59.115
What did he give you?

34:01.000 --> 34:02.536
A bike, once.

34:02.540 --> 34:04.997
Was that one that you had asked for?

34:06.170 --> 34:09.207
No. It was a BMX.

34:09.620 --> 34:10.996
Any others?

34:17.540 --> 34:19.326
My catcher's mitt from today.

34:27.620 --> 34:29.531
What did he do?

34:30.380 --> 34:32.325
You can tell me.

34:35.210 --> 34:37.417
He used to...

34:38.170 --> 34:39.819
He used to bite me.

34:42.460 --> 34:44.997
He hasn't for a while.

34:47.080 --> 34:49.071
But he did...

34:51.580 --> 34:53.536
He did other things.

34:54.080 --> 34:56.116
Will you let the doctor take a look?

34:57.120 --> 34:59.532
Maybe we can match dental records.

35:02.250 --> 35:03.410
Okay.

35:04.880 --> 35:06.700
What about a few years ago?

35:07.080 --> 35:09.378
In 2004, did he give you anything?

35:13.880 --> 35:16.246
That's the year he gave me Randy.

35:16.710 --> 35:17.916
Randy?

35:18.580 --> 35:20.241
My dog.

35:20.250 --> 35:22.161
He was just a puppy then.

35:22.170 --> 35:24.491
Guys, Sam's father gave her gifts,

35:24.500 --> 35:26.070
trophies, from each abduction.

35:26.080 --> 35:27.320
That's significant.

35:27.330 --> 35:29.412
I didn't know that's what they were.

35:29.670 --> 35:32.321
We need to find out if Angel
had a puppy the day he was taken.

35:32.330 --> 35:34.787
Yeah.

35:34.790 --> 35:35.996
That's right.

35:36.000 --> 35:38.821
Some of the neighbors were
giving them away that day.

35:38.830 --> 35:41.287
They had a whole box.

35:41.290 --> 35:43.872
But I wouldn't let the boys keep one.

35:43.880 --> 35:45.108
Hotch, you hear that?

35:45.120 --> 35:46.826
Yes. Thanks, JJ.

35:46.830 --> 35:48.036
Wait, Hotch, um...

35:49.580 --> 35:51.411
We're trying to get a dental match.

35:51.420 --> 35:53.069
He's got old bite marks on him.

35:54.540 --> 35:56.030
What is it?

35:56.040 --> 35:57.450
Oh, my...

35:57.460 --> 35:59.951
My dad has his teeth
recapped a few years ago.

35:59.960 --> 36:01.450
He said something like,

36:01.460 --> 36:03.246
"That's what happens when
you get older," or whatever.

36:03.250 --> 36:04.569
He made a joke about it.

36:21.540 --> 36:23.872
You better not give me any trouble.

36:23.880 --> 36:26.030
No! No!

36:29.580 --> 36:31.207
We're heading to Allen's house.

36:31.210 --> 36:33.075
You think he's got
a secondary location?

36:33.080 --> 36:35.457
He could, but guys like him
